<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Arngren Website Analysis</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>

<body>

    <h1>Website Evaluation: Arngren.net</h1>

    <div class="grid-container">

        <!-- USER EXPERIENCE -->
        <div class="grid-item">
            <h2>User Experience</h2>
            <p>
                The user experience of arngren.net is confusing and overwhelming.
                The homepage contains too many images, texts, and links displayed
                at the same time. Navigation is unclear, making it difficult for
                users to find products or information quickly.
            </p>

            <p>
                The design looks outdated and lacks consistency in fonts,
                colors, and layout. Users may feel lost because clickable
                elements are not easily recognizable.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- CONTENT -->
        <div class="grid-item">
            <h2>Content</h2>
            <p>
                The website contains a large amount of product information,
                images, and advertisements. However, the content is poorly
                organized and lacks structure.
            </p>

            <p>
                Important information is mixed with unrelated items,
                making it hard for users to focus. The excessive text
                and graphics reduce readability and clarity.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- GRID LAYOUT -->
        <div class="grid-item">
            <h2>Grid Layout</h2>
            <p>
                The grid layout appears chaotic and unstructured.
                Elements are not aligned properly and there is
                little spacing between items.
            </p>

            <p>
                The website lacks visual hierarchy, causing
                products and information to look randomly placed.
                This makes scanning the page difficult and affects
                usability negatively.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>

</body>
</html>
